  "content": "Sophisticated investors argue that leverage itself is not risky if applied to low-volatility, diversified portfolios with conservative haircuts (e.g., risk parity). The risk lies in mismatched liquidity (borrowing short to invest in illiquid assets) and lack of stress testing, not leverage per se.",
